# H5W-BUILD.md — Build Queue

This file is the primary work source when §BUILD-LOOP is active. The
autoloop reads it, picks the next TODO (or the IN-PROGRESS task if one
exists), and continues until all entries are DONE or BLOCKED.

**Status values:**
- `TODO` — not yet started
- `IN-PROGRESS` — actively being built (only one at a time)
- `BLOCKED` — waiting on external dependency (note the blocker)
- `DONE` — implemented + verified + committed (move to # Completed)

**Phase discipline:** Each feature is broken into 2-5 phases. A phase is
DONE only when the code builds clean, the new functionality is exercised
at least once, and the change is committed per `.h5w/git-policy`. "I
wrote the code" alone is IN-PROGRESS, not DONE.

